name: Don Toliver
biography: Houston-born melodic rapper known for atmospheric trap beats, auto-tuned hooks, and a blend of club-ready anthems with moody late-night textures.

name: Justin Bieber
biography: Global pop artist blending R&B-infused vocals with radio-ready choruses, evolving from acoustic roots to sleek contemporary productions.

name: Future
biography: Atlanta icon delivering hypnotic flows over trap production, mixing introspective melodies with high-energy club records.

name: Rihanna
biography: Barbadian superstar known for genre-hopping hits across pop, R&B, and dance, pairing bold vocals with trend-setting style.

name: The Weeknd
biography: Canadian singer blending dark R&B, pop, and electronic influences with cinematic production and falsetto-driven hooks.

name: Bruno Mars
biography: Hawaii-born showman delivering retro-leaning pop with soul, funk, and polished vocal performances.

name: Black Eyed Peas
biography: Los Angeles group fusing hip hop, pop, and electronic hooks into arena-ready party anthems.

name: Sean Paul
biography: Jamaican dancehall icon pairing patois-heavy sing-rap with club-ready riddims and global crossover collaborations.

name: Romeo Santos
biography: Bronx-born bachata star leading smooth Latin ballads with heartfelt storytelling and guitar-led arrangements.

name: Akon
biography: Singer-songwriter blending R&B hooks with pop and Afrobeat influences, known for chart-topping collaborations and soulful anthems.
